# Multiphysics Helmet Optimization Project

## Project Overview
This project focused on designing and evaluating a protective helmet model using Fusion 360 and SimScale. The goal was to analyze the helmet’s structural performance and airflow behavior through static structural and CFD simulations.

## Tools Used
- Fusion 360
- SimScale
- CFD
- Static Structural Analysis

## Simulation Work
### Structural Analysis
- Evaluated stress distribution and displacement under loading conditions.
- Reviewed von Mises stress behavior to identify high-stress regions.

### CFD Analysis
- Analyzed airflow behavior and pressure distribution around the helmet geometry.
- Evaluated aerodynamic characteristics using CFD simulations.

## Key Skills Demonstrated
- CAD Modeling
- CFD
- FEA
- Engineering Design
- Mesh Refinement
